**[imports]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion import Mathlib.NumberTheory.Cyclotomic.PID import Mathlib.NumberTheory.Cyclotomic.PrimitiveRoots ```
I hate these gymnastics...
I don't see how we can avoid it. Using `Fact` works quite well in the general case, but here I don't think we can do something better.

I think the root cause of this is the decision to use `PNat`s in the cyclotomic part of the library.
In any case, it may make sense to add `Fact (Nat.Prime (p : PNat))` instances at least for small explicit `p` (and perhaps also something like `instance {p : Nat} [hp: Fact p.Prime] : Fact [Nat.Prime (Nat.toPNat p hp.out.pos)] := ...`.)
I don't think we use `Fact` in global instance. For example [Nat.prime_three](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime.html#Nat.prime_three) is a regular theorem.

```lean
instance : Fact (Nat.Prime 3) := inferInstance
```
works.
[Nat.fact_prime_three](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Nat/Prime.html#Nat.fact_prime_three) (and similar for `2`).
Ops, I've missed that!

I've added those (also for `5`). It's a little unfortunate that we don't current use [PNat.Prime](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/PNat/Prime.html#PNat.Prime) (what we use is of course defeq, but we write the definition by hand). I will maybe refactor this, but in another PR.
And of course we can try to remove `PNat` from the cyclotomic stuff, but that is going to be a lot of work I think.
There should be a `simp` lemma that does `((3 : â„•+) : â„•) = 3` for all positive values of `3`. But I cannot figure out how to spell it so that it works.

Can you add
```lean
@[simp]
lemma PNat.val_ofNat (n : â„•) : ((no_index (OfNat.ofNat n.succ) : â„•+) : â„•) = n.succ := rfl
```
at a suitable place and then use it here?
Done, thanks for the suggestion!

Is it not possible to deduce this with an instance going from `Fact (p : â„•+).Prime` to `Fact ((p : â„•+) : â„•).Prime`?

Something like this:
```
instance {p : â„•+} [h : Fact p.Prime] : Fact (p : â„•).Prime := h
```
Trying it.
